result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 15CF207, 15CM311 & 15CM351 called at 2:46 pm [sf]  (case was set for initial appearance)
Defendant Tianna N. Mizener in court with Attorney Sylvie Dahnert. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

On cases 15CM311 & 15CM351 :
Service of Complaint admitted; reading waived.

ADA Hall files amended information in 15CF207.

On Case 15CF207:
Constitutional rights given; pleas of "Guilty" entered on Counts 1, 2, 3 & 4 of the Amended Information; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Case 15CM351:
Constitutional rights given; pleas of "Guilty" entered on Count 1 & 2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses 15CM311.

On each Count, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 3 years, each count concurrent, with conditions:
--AODA assessment & follow through with recommended treatment per agent
--Maintain Absolute sobriety from all alcohol, and illegal drugs
--Any other assessment, treatment or counseling per agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program or combination of the two, per Agent
--No possession of any non-prescribed controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
--The defendant shall take her medications only as prescribed by her treating physician
--The defendant shall undergo any psychiatric or psychological assessment as directed by DOC
-- No acts or threats of violence
--To submitt DNA sample to DOC or designee
--To pay statutory costs 
--To pay DNA surcharges
